    "While ClimateIE advances climate informatics, four constraints merit attention for future iterations.",
    "Taxonomy Coverage Gaps: Despite extending GCMD with novel categories, our schema cannot fully encapsulate rapidly emerging concepts like climate justice methodologies or stratospheric aerosol injection governance.",
    "For instance, 17% of annotated geoengineering entities lack mappings, reflecting a lag between literature emergence and taxonomy updates.",
    "Entity Linking Precision-Throughput Tradeoffs: Our fuzzy string matching for Wikidata integration (Levenshtein ≤30%) prioritizes broad coverage over precision, yielding false positives for polysemous terms-e.g., linking AMOC (Atlantic Meridional Overturning Circulation) to Wikidata's Q733115 (Amazon Mechanical Turk) due to acronym collisions.",
    "While threshold tuning (0.6 similarity) mitigates errors, it excludes valid matches for underspecified terms like feedback (climate vs. control systems)."
